leg*.\ni Tax Cut Urged!\nI a\ni By Economist\nEconomist Robert Nathan,\ntoday told AFL-CIO leaders\nI here economic recovery will ye\nquire an 88 to 810 billion eut\nin taxes.\ni The former Government 1\neconomist spoke before 200\nlabor leaders attending an In-\nI dustrlat Union Department\nconference on ways to meet the\nchallenge of automaUon at the\nbargaining table,\ni 'To get speedy recovery.\"\nsaid Mr. Nathan In his address\nt at the Statler Hotel, \"there are\ntwo steps which must be taken\npromptly. One is a substantial\ni temporary decrease In taxes of\nt 88 to 810 billion, primarily de\nsigned to increase the buying\ni power of the middle and lower\nincome groups. Talk about\ncutting taxes for the high\nIncome groups and corpora\nlions to stimulate Investment\nat a time when capacity is al\nready excessive makes little\nsense.\n41 Locals Get\nAutonomy in\nTeamsters\nThe Teamsters Union reports\nIt has released 41 locals from\ntrusteeship In the last six\nmonths, and another 22 locals\nare in process of regaining the#\nautonomy.\nYesterday's official announce\nment confirmed a report by\nThe Star earlier this month\nThe 41 locals still In trustee\nship have only 2.4 per cent of\nthe Teamsters' membership of\n1.5 million, according to the\nreport. Six months.ago. when\n104 locals were in trusteeship,'\nNON-STOPS\n\nPHONE ST 3-3220\nISSSSSBm\n\u2022J per cent of the membership\nfell in this category.\n\u201cAutonomy will be restored\nas soon as possible In each\ncase, consistent with the beat\nInterests of the members of\nthese locals.\" the union said.\nThe Senate Racket* Commit\ntee \u2014which describes trusteeship\nas \"servitude\" has charged\nTeamsters' leaders with abusing\nthe system to consolidate their\npower. The union said Presi\ndent James R. Hoffa wants to\nrelease locals from trusteeship\nas soon as possible.\nI When a local la in trusteeship.\nI international headquarters aa-\nsigns an qfllctal to handle Its\naffairs.\nAccording to the breakdown\nfurnished by the Teamster*\nyesterday, Mr. Hoffa personally\nstill Is trustee for eight locals.\nTHE EVENING STAR. Washington, D. C.\nTtigsDAr. scan strifes\nI NEW YORK MOST SUPERB I\nHOTEL LOCATION\njj Central Pars I 1\nK enchanting vlewe In ev*-y <tlra\u00abtlon,\nclose to thaatraa, Bth Avenue Shopa I\nand the Collaaum. Oracloua dining 1 U (^B]\nIn world famous ftumpslmaysr\u2019s and\nthe Case de la Pals.\nIn WASMINOTON. CAU IXststlvs 1-MSI J\nfar raen. reservation* i\nI pl.t-EH ye 11 j W\nfk,f 'TsT\u2019rTW\nKiwtynki onljTZjy\nu&MtmBJL MZI\nMliWi 1 JO CINTSAt CASK SOUTH\nf* Chanaa O 1 i\u00bb>o- *-\u00ab\u00bb,oant\nA-7","height":"29446","width":"18755"}}
